  "prompt": "Can we eat Apple at night?",
  "response": "Yes, you can eat apples at night. Apples are a healthy snack option that provides fiber, vitamins, and antioxidants. Eating them in moderation can be beneficial at any time of day, including at night. Some people find that eating fruits close to bedtime may cause discomfort or indigestion, but this can vary from person to person. If you enjoy apples in the evening and they don't bother your stomach, feel free to include them in your nighttime snacks!",
